"–Female":"Deceased","1119–1143":"1119–1143","1085–1145":"1085–1145","1028–1080":"1028–1080","1034–Female":"1034–Deceased","1080":"1080","about 1060":"about 1060","about 1085":"about 1085","1143":"1143","1085":"1085","1051":"1051","1094":"1094","1060":"1060","1028":"1028","1145":"1145","1046":"1046","1034":"1034","about 1145":"about 1145","1119":"1119","nameMeanings":[{"name":"von","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Vaughan  .","Chinese: variant of   Wong  .","Cambodian: written វ៉ុន, unexplained."],"variants":[{"name":"Vaughan","meanings":["Welsh: from <i>fychan</i>, a lenited form of <i>bychan</i>, a diminutive of <i>bach</i> ‘little’. This was often used to distinguish the younger of two bearers of the same personal name, typically the son of a father with the same name."]}]},{"name":"Abenberg","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: habitational name from any of several places called Rabenberg, as for example in Saxony or Lower Saxony."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Otto","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a short form of any of the various Germanic compound personal names containing the element <i>od</i>, <i>ot</i> ‘prosperity, wealth’ (  compare the corresponding Old English <i>ēad</i> in names such as  Edward   and   Edwin  ).  St Otto of Bamberg  (  d. 1139 ) was a missionary to the Pomeranians.  Otto the Great  (  912–73 ) is generally regarded as the founder of the Holy Roman Empire, and the name has been borne by several members of German and Austrian royal houses. It was recorded occasionally among immigrants to England from the Low Countries in the 14th century, but failed to establish itself. Since the 19th century it has again been used occasionally in the English-speaking world, mostly among immigrants from Germanic countries."],"variants":[]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["1  ♂ ‘Wondrous’ or ‘enlightenment’.","2  ♀ ‘Fine jade’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Otto II von Abenberg was born about 1060, his father, Babo II von Abensperg, was 34 and his mother, n.n., was 27. He married n.n. about 1085. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1145, at the age of 87."},"et":{"about 1060–about 1145":"umbes 1060–umbes 1145","1046–1051":"1046–1051","1060–1145":"1060–1145","–1094":"–1094","–Female":"Surnud","1119–1143":"1119–1143","1085–1145":"1085–1145","1028–1080":"1028–1080","1034–Female":"1034–Surnud","1080":"1080","about 1060":"umbes 1060","about 1085":"umbes 1085","1143":"1143","1085":"1085","1051":"1051","1094":"1094","1060":"1060","1028":"1028","1145":"1145","1046":"1046","1034":"1034","about 1145":"umbes 1145","1119":"1119"},"fi":{"about 1060–about 1145":"noin 1060–noin 1145","1046–1051":"1046–1051","1060–1145":"1060–1145","–1094":"–1094","–Female":"Kuollut","1119–1143":"1119–1143","1085–1145":"1085–1145","1028–1080":"1028–1080","1034–Female":"1034–Kuollut","1080":"1080","about 1060":"noin 1060","about 1085":"noin 1085","1143":"1143","1085":"1085","1051":"1051","1094":"1094","1060":"1060","1028":"1028","1145":"1145","1046":"1046","1034":"1034","about 1145":"noin 1145","1119":"1119"},"fr":{"about 1060–about 1145":"environ 1060–environ 1145","1046–1051":"1046–1051","1060–1145":"1060–1145","–1094":"–1094","–Female":"Décédée","1119–1143":"1119–1143","1085–1145":"1085–1145","1028–1080":"1028–1080","1034–Female":"1034–Décédée","1080":"1080","about 1060":"environ 1060","about 1085":"environ 1085","1143":"1143","1085":"1085","1051":"1051","1094":"1094","1060":"1060","1028":"1028","1145":"1145","1046":"1046","1034":"1034","about 1145":"environ 1145","1119":"1119","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Otto II von Abenberg est né environ 1060, son père, B